Review: 
Britain&#039;s foremost multi award winning joke technician Jimmy Carr returns with his fourth live stand up DVD, Jimmy Carr In Concert.

No one writes sharper jokes and no one delivers them better than Jimmy. He commands his audience with twisted little aphorisms, "the sort of thing you might find in a fortune cookie baked by Satan" with no-one escaping his biting wit and take no prisoners approach to subject matter.

Recorded live at London&#039;s Bloomsbury Theatre, Jimmy walks a fine line with truly outrageous gags that would be thoroughly offensive if not so expertly delivered with an ironic glint in his eye.

As Jimmy explains: "This DVD is exactly the same as last year&#039;s except every single word. It&#039;s rude, crude and offensive but those aren&#039;t the only reasons you&#039;ll enjoy it."
